{"outcome":{"note":{}},"id":"24-825","ticketId":"24","phase":"planning","detail":"---\n\n## Planning Report — Issue #24: Remove dead SwiftLint rule from init template\n\n### 1. Language \/ Framework \/ Stack\n\n- **Language**: Go (module `github.com\/iksnae\/code-certification`, `go 1.25.5`)\n- **CLI framework**: `github.com\/spf13\/cobra`\n- **YAML**: `gopkg.in\/yaml.v3`\n- **Build**: `go build .\/cmd\/certify\/`\n- **Test**: `go test .\/... -count=1`\n\n### 2. Relevant code location (what to change)\n\n**File**: `cmd\/certify\/init_cmd.go`\n\n**Exact block to remove** — lines **709–716** (the `lint-clean` rule inside `swiftStandardPolicy`):\n\n```\n  - id: lint-clean\n    dimension: correctness\n    description: \"SwiftLint must report zero errors\"\n    severity: error\n    metric: lint_errors\n    threshold: 0\n\n```\n\nThat's 7 lines of rule-YAML plus 1 trailing blank line. The surrounding constant (`swiftStandardPolicy`, lines 704–738) is the **only** place in the codebase that references \"SwiftLint\". After removal, the `swiftStandardPolicy` will have 3 rules: `test-pass`, `no-todos`, `max-complexity`.\n\n### 3. Why this rule is dead (confirmed)\n\n- **No SwiftLint collector exists** anywhere in the codebase. A full search for `SwiftLint`, `swiftlint`, and `swift` across `internal\/evidence\/lint.go`, `internal\/engine\/scorer.go`, and all `.go` files returned zero matches for any Swift linter integration.\n- **`language_tiers.go` does not exist** — the issue's suggested comment references a file that isn't in the repo.\n- The only other Swift reference in Go code is in `internal\/doctor\/doctor.go` (LSP-based, not SwiftLint).\n- Parent issue #21 confirmed this rule causes **fabricated grades** for Swift repos: 213 Swift units get identical scores because `lint_errors` is never collected, triggering \"missing evidence\" violations.\n\n### 4. Call sites \/ dependents (what NOT to touch)\n\n- **Other language policies** in the same file — `lint-clean` rules in `goStandardPolicy` (line 281), `tsStandardPolicy` (line 318), `pythonStandardPolicy` (line 458), `rustStandardPolicy` (line 542), and elsewhere (line 626) — these are **live** (backed by real collectors) and are **explicitly non-goals per the issue**.\n- **`testdata\/policies\/swift-standard.yml`** — also has the dead `lint-clean` rule (lines 10–16) but is a **separate fixture** used only by `config.LoadPolicyPacks` which doesn't inspect rule content. Tests don't compare init output to this fixture. The issue limits targets to `cmd\/certify\/init_cmd.go` only.\n- **`scorer.go`** and **report generation** — non-goals, not touched.\n- **Test files** — no test directly references `swiftStandardPolicy`'s content. `TestLanguagePolicy_AllSupported` only checks the return is non-empty. All other `lint-clean` test references use inline rules (not the Swift template).\n\n### 5. Recommended approach for implementer\n\n**Remove the 8-line block entirely** (the 7 YAML lines + the trailing blank). This is cleaner than comment-wrapping because:\n- `language_tiers.go` doesn't exist yet (the proposed comment would reference a non-existent file)\n- The rule is actively harmful (fabricated grades per issue #21)\n- It's trivially re-addable if\/when a SwiftLint collector lands\n\nThe resulting `swiftStandardPolicy` will start its `rules:` section at `test-pass`:\n\n```go\nconst swiftStandardPolicy = `name: swift-standard\nversion: \"1.0.0\"\nlanguage: swift\n\nrules:\n  - id: test-pass\n    dimension: testability\n    ...\n```\n\n### 6. Verification\n\n```bash\ngo build .\/cmd\/certify\/   # must compile clean\ngo test .\/... -count=1    # must pass (no test references the removed block)\n```\n\nNo test should break — `TestLanguagePolicy_AllSupported` checks for non-empty return only, and `TestInitCmd`\/`TestInitCmd_Idempotent` verify directory structure and file existence, not policy content.","at":805829437.03067}
